text.section:
The program of operation shall provide for:
establishment of adequate service facilities and other necessary facilities;
management of the Association;
assessment of Association members to defray losses and expenses;
commission arrangements;
reasonable and objective underwriting standards;
acceptance and cession of reinsurance;
procedures to determine amounts of insurance to be provided;
immediate binding of eligible risks;
a premium installment plan; and
notwithstanding Title 27, Subtitle 6 of this article, underwriting guidelines and procedures that allow the Association to shorten the cancellation period for policies of essential property insurance and homeowner's insurance for certain conditions that are determined to exist.
